summary: This is an FBI 302 form documenting a telephonic interview conducted on March 23, 2021, with an unnamed individual. The interviewee discusses their experience with media inquiries, their vague interactions with an unnamed male attorney, and provides information about Eva Dubin and Ghislaine Maxwell in relation to Jeffrey Epstein.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Mentioned by the interviewee, who states they are 'not sure about' her, indicating she is a subject of discussion in the interview.

persons.name: Eva Dubin
persons.context: Described by the interviewee as a Swedish woman ('Ms Sweden Lady') whom Epstein bragged about. She and her husband were on flights with Epstein, but the interviewee does not recall her being involved in massages.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Central figure discussed; the interviewee mentions Epstein bragging about Eva Dubin and that an attorney was more interested in him than other participants.

connections.description: Epstein knew Dubin, bragged that she was 'Ms Sweden,' and she and her husband were on flights with him.
Both are key figures in the case, discussed together in the context of the interview.

events.title: FBI Telephonic Interview
events.description: An FBI agent conducts a telephonic interview with an unnamed individual, who discusses media contacts, legal representation, and associations with Jeffrey Epstein, Ghislaine Maxwell, and Eva Dubin.

locations: New York, New York, United States
keyFacts: The document is an FBI 302 form from an interview conducted on March 23, 2021, with an individual whose identity is protected.
The interviewee received numerous calls from journalists regarding the Epstein case, obtained an attorney, and the calls subsequently stopped.
The interviewee met Eva Dubin, a Swedish woman described by Epstein as 'Ms Sweden,' at Epstein's house and recalled her and her husband being on flights with Epstein.
The interviewee stated they were vague with an unnamed male attorney who was more interested in Jeffrey Epstein than other participants.
The document is subject to a protective order restricting the distribution of specific paragraphs.
